This was the initial water quality test.  Training was being conducted by Donna Sefton.  Secchi rope was only 30 feet long- ran out of rope before secchi disappeared.
Bright sunny day with hint of fall- rain from saturday to wednesday 9-13
Partly cloudy- cool day and very calm waters
Partly cloudy- cool- breezy day- 60 degrees- Pumps have not been running for about 2 months.  Tom Miller also helped on this date
Cool50's- breezy- sunny day.  Not a cloud in the sky. Rained yesterday- Pumps have been  running about 2 days).
Approximately 80 Degrees- cloudy to partly cloudy and windy
Partly cloudy- warm- light breeze- lake slightly wavy- temp mid 80s- heavy air feels like 90s- pumps are running- turned on around May 15.  Chris Mangano helped on this date
Partly cloudly- quite breezy- absolutely perfect summer day- pumps are running- extremely dry in the area. Chris and Tony Mangano helped on this date.
Water very high- severe flooding in the area. 5-10 inches of rain in the area in the 5 days preceding this date.
Clear-80 F- Beautiful morning on DHL
Clear day- slight wind- pumps not running-sun shining- no boats on lake except ours
Humid- record temp. 80-90 last couple days- pumps not on-slight breeze- few fishermen on lake- beautiful day.
Highest water level in about 14 years- Cumulus clouds- blustery-high wind(cool)-sunshine-part of sky showing blue.
Beautiful breezy day-mostly currus clouds- some cumulus-severe flooding in area-More than 12 inches of rain on June 7 and 8.  Water went over lake spillway for several days.
Beautiful sunny day-very calm-dock pier still under water-no clouds-open lake drain valve on  72208.
Overcast all morning- Some blue skies and susshine at 12:30 P.M..  Lake valve closed- quiet- calm day.  Water still slightly high- no wake taken off lake about 3 week ago.
Bright sunny day- temp in mid to high 50's-beautiful bright fall day-no pumps all summer/
first spring like day in a few weeks- sunshine- partly cloudy- pumps not running
Partly overcast day- partly sunny- beautiful day - pumps not running.  Town of LaValle Police patrolling.
overcast - nice summer day- rain predicted - pumps running.  First year of purple seed floating in the water.
Dale- Dennis- Terry:  clear day- pumps not running- Terry got information on the testing procedure.
Pumps off.  Eurasian Milfoil heavy in Woodland landing area.  Day after Labor Day.  Lake took a beating.  Nice day.
Clear day.  Pumps running.  Last reading for the year.
